In both CoQuAD and Natural Questions datasets Google\-SDA has a an RP above 90%, albeit for very low coverage, whereas QAnswer has a high coverage, more than 96% in all datasets with poor RP. {\mysystem} not only provides a high coverage, but also a decent RP, with the improved version increasing RP by 10% on CoQuAD. Except on the LCQuAD dataset, {\mysystem} provides a better trade-off than the baselines.